</link>
<description>
<p>Book telling the father-son story of a motorcycle trip across the western United States was published in 1974 and quickly became a best-seller</p><p>Robert Pirsig, author of the influential 1970s philosophical novel <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2000/jul/23/1">Zen and the Art of Motorcycle Maintenance</a>, has died at the age of 88.</p><p>Peter Hubbard, executive editor of his publisher William Morrow &amp; Co, said in a statement that Pirsig’s wife Wendy had confirmed his death at his home in Maine “after a period of failing health”.</p> <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2017/apr/25/robert-pirsig-zen-and-the-art-of-motorcycle-maintenance-author-dies-aged-88">Continue reading...</a>
