</link>
<description>
<p>My wife Jane Eccles, who has died of cancer aged 58, was an artist who worked widely in the world of illustration, from magazine editorial work and advertising to books for many publishers.</p><p>She wrote and illustrated Maxwell Monster, in 1991, and increasingly specialised in illustrating books for children. Jane forged a fruitful relationship with the publisher Macmillan, for whom she filled the pages of children’s poetry and joke books with her warm and witty drawings.</p> <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2017/apr/18/jane-eccles-obituary">Continue reading...</a>
